# assessment-scoring-flows

Key Assessment Scoring Systems:

## Risk Assessment (RiskAssessment.tsx)
Importance Score: 85
- HYRNA scoring implementation across 8 domains
- Domain weightings: prior offending (0.3), family (0.15), education (0.1), peer relations (0.15), substance use (0.1), recreation (0.05), personality (0.1), attitudes (0.05)
- Risk level thresholds:
  - Very Low: 0-15%
  - Low: 16-30% 
  - Low Medium: 30-44%
  - Medium: 44-58%
  - Medium High: 58-72%
  - High: 72-86%
  - Very High: >86%

## Real Colors Personality Assessment (ColorAssessment.tsx) 
Importance Score: 75
- Forced-choice ranking across 6 trait groups
- Four personality dimensions: Heart, Anchor, Mind, Spark
- Primary/secondary style determination from cumulative scores
- Maps personality types to staff interaction guidelines

## Individual Service Plan Assessment (QuickISPAssessment.tsx)
Importance Score: 70
- Treatment goal categorization system
- Early warning sign tracking
- Intervention effectiveness scoring
- Progress tracking with customizable measures
- Staff approach mapping by personality type

## Assessment Integration Rules
- All assessments feed youth risk calculations
- Results determine treatment level assignments
- Historical assessment change tracking
- Auto-save with domain validation
- Required reassessment scheduling

